title: First load
description: When first loading, the database is empty and an alert will be raised. You can check the DB in the "Application" tab of developer tools. (ctrl+shift+i)

title: Main Screen
description: Here you'll find a list of presentations. You can edit, add or delete them from here.

title: Add New
description:
Clicking the "Add New" in the main screen button opens an editing menu.
Here you can add new registers to the DB

title: Fields
description:
The Carts editing screen has several fields.
The name of the cart.
An emoji icon for that cart
A brief description of the cart
The server path to the slides data. This will be updated with local files if not present.

title: Saving
description:
After clicking the save button, an alert window will show and the screen will update with the new fields.
You can also click on the fields titles to update and sort the view.

title: Deleting
description:
You can mark a field for deletion clicking the delete button.
The field index number will be marked
the delete button will be updated with an Unmark one
and a Erase button will appear at the bottom.

title: Editing slides
description:
To setup the slides go to the menu bar (click the top left icon if the menu is folded)
The first option, slides. Will bring you to the slides editing interface.

title: New
description:
If you didn't imported data or just used the projector, the db will be empty.
As in the main screen, clck the add new button.

title: Slides fieds
description:
After the title field is a IMG placeholder. Drop an image file or click in the placeholder to open a file menu to insert one.
In the description field you can use HTML tags to link pages or format text.
You can chek to add several effects after.
